Currently on Android devices, users can backup & restore Installed Apps with our app. The App Archives of different versions can be coexisting. A new feature that can also backup Contacts, SMS and Call Log is upcoming. App Backup & Restore cannot backup & restore the data of apps (such as your chat history), but only the APK files (installation packages). App data can be saved only through third party account login or app account. App Backup & Restore is NOT able to save game record due to system restriction.

"Please choose either one of the following methods: 1) Tap Apps in main screen – choose apps - click Backup at bottom left corner 2)Tap Backup in bottom left of the main screen – select apps – click Backup"

"Please choose either one of the following methods: 1) Tap Archives in main screen – select Current – click Restore at bottom left corner – click Yes to install 2) Tap Restore at bottom of the main screen – select Archives – click Restore"
Go to System Setting – Applications – enable Unknown Sources – try restore apps again.

Backup apps will saved into the internal storage by default. If external SD card exists, the backup path can be changed and edited in Settings – Backup settings – Archived path – set. The former backup path settings will not be changed if users upgrade to a new version of App Backup & Restore.

For Android 4.4 and above, Google reserved the permission to write plug-in SD card. It is now granted only for Google and cellphone manufactures. For Android 4.4 or 5.0, the only path that Google reserved to developers is as below： /storage/extSdCard/Android/data/mobi.infolife.appbackup/ Please follow that path to backup apps to external SD card. In addition, the support of SAF (Storage Access Framework) is functional for Android 5.0+ devices. If there is a SAF setting page pops-up during changing the path, please follow the guide and you will be covered.

"Auto-Backup Apps will automatically backup itself every time when updating. To turn it on, go to Apps in main screen – touch & hold a specific app – switch on Set as Auto Backup. At the same time, a system notification will pop-up, reminding that a new archive has been generated. Switch it off when you want to stop the Auto-Backup of this app."

Apps, Archives, and Media Files (photos, music and videos) are Currently fully supported. In upcoming versions, Contacts, SMS and Call logs transferring will be available.
Yes. Please select the apps/media files – click the share button at the upright corner – select the send-to destination.
App Backup & Restore uses device’s player to open photos/music/videos. Please check the device player or download a better player.
No. App Backup & Restore builds a private network using self-build Wi-Fi hotspot which enables transfer/share free of mobile charge, data, nor cables.

"Send: please choose either one of the following methods to send. 1) Select Apps/ Archives /Media in main screen – select apps, Archives, photos, music, videos – click Send – wait for receiver – select receiver – start sending 2) Select Send at the bottom of the main screen – select apps, packages, photos, music, videos – click Send – wait for receiver – select receiver – start sending Receive: Select Receive at the bottom of the main screen – wait for sender – start receiving."

"Received apps will be added in Archives. Received photos/music/video will be added to Media. Check the red dot or new marks in front of the icons, those are the new income files that you just received."
No. However it takes longer time to transfer/share a larger file.

Users can only transfer apps/media with devices which install App Backup & Restore. The app creates its own Wi-Fi hotspot which enables charge-free file transfer. Users can invite friends and send the app by click Friends button at the left upper corner without any data consume.

"Please try the following methods: 1.Turn on the Location/GPS service so that the devices can recognize each other. 2. Make sure the devices are connecting successfully. 3.Put devices closer and close unnecessary networking applications. 4.Move the devices to areas which have less signal interference."

There are many factors influences the transferring speed, for example the Wi-Fi environment, physical distance between two devices, the reading speed of memory card or the operation state of the phone. Please put devices closer, close unnecessary networking applications and move to an environment with less interference.
The transferring process is private via Wi-Fi hotspot without insecure external web environment. No malware/vulnerability exists during the share process.

"App Backup & Restore is a free Android application which allows users to backup, restore, transfer, share apps/files among Android devices. Backup apps to save more space, restore them when needed, transfer apps/files between all devices and share apps/files with friends easy & fast, without mobile data & cables."

"Apps: all installed apps will appear here. Packages: all backup apps will appear here. Media: all photos, music, video saved in your device will appear here, media files saved in third-party apps are not included. Personal: will be available in future versions, may include contacts, SMS, call logs, etc. History: view your history action here, check how often you need to backup your apps. Rooted: will be available in future versions."
